Removal of Concrete Wall in Korean Peninsula Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The Swiss Committee for Supporting Korea's Independent and Peaceful Reunification issued a statement on December 30 last year demanding the removal of the anti-reunification concrete wall built in the area south of the Military Demarcation Line (MDL) of Korea and sent a letter of protest to the south Korean chief executive.
 Holding that the wall bisecting the Korean Peninsula, built by the former dictators of south Korea, should be pulled down, the committee said in the statement: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wall remains a leftover of confrontation contrary to the present times when detente and cooperation are going on between the north and the south of Korea after the historic inter-Korean summit meeting was held in June 2000 and the June 15 joint declaration adopted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The achievements made so far in the efforts for national reunification--reconnection of severed rail and road links in the MDL area, reunion of separated families and relatives, etc.--prove that the wall is no longer necessary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present authorities of south Korea should not talk about the spirit of the north-south joint declaration and the reunification of the peninsula, but pull down the anti-national, anti-reunification wall for their realization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the protest letter the organization contended that the south Korean chief executive should demolish the disgraceful wall if he truly hopes for reconciliation with the north and for the implementation of the joint declaration. 
 If the concrete wall remains as it is, the south Korean authorities will be condemned by the fellow countrymen, it warned, strongly urging the chief executive to immediately stop following the U.S.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Removing Main Obstacle to Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- It is attributable to the U.S. that occasions to open a turning phase of national reunification between the north and the south of Korea were provided in the days of the over 60-year-long hard-fought struggle but they were not contributable to developing the reunification movement and the tragedy of national division has continued. 
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a by-lined article today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the U.S. started its military occupation of south Korea by landing its troops of aggression in Inchon on Sept. 8, 1945, it has divided the Korean Peninsula into the north and the south and viciously blocked the efforts of the Korean nation for reconciliation, unity and reunification.
 The U.S. strategy toward Korea to bisect and dominate the Korean Peninsula and pursue its aggressive interests remains unchanged at the present times whose trend is independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality requires all the Koreans to heighten vigilance against the U.S. anti-reunification moves to turn back the developing situation of the Korean Peninsula and decisively counter them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to lead the road of independent reunification provided with so much effort to a final victory all the Koreans should decisively foil the U.S. imperialists' moves of aggression, interference and obstruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation has the strength and ability to smash the anti-reunification and war moves of the outsiders and invigorate the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity is strength and guarantees all victories. No force on earth can match the strength of the nation rallied as one, believing in its own strength.
 Only victory is in store for the Korean nation conducting a vigorous three-point patriotic movement under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself" no matter how hard the foreign forces are working to block the cause of national reunification.

Tradition of Supporting Army, Helping People
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- The fine traits of Songun Korea that the people assist the army and vice versa should be brought into fuller bloom, says the joint New Year editorial.
 The tradition of supporting army and helping people, the source of strength for the ever-victorious Korean revolution, was established during the hard-fought anti-Japanese armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From the first days of the guerrilla warfare, President Kim Il Sung, with "As fish cannot live without water, so guerrillas cannot live without the people" as his creed, educated the members of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army (KPRA) in the ardent love for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They avoided battles that might do damage to people and used to help them in their work while dropping in at residential quarters.
 Once people sent an ox to guerrillas who ran out provisions, they sent it back to the owner. Even on the verge of death from starvation and cold, they did not inflict even the slightest loss on people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The noble spiritual world of the KPRA members, who valued and protected the lives and property of the people, made them assist the army with sincerity.
 Seeing the people assisting the army at the cost of their lives, the guerrillas keenly realized the ardent love of the people for the revolutionary army and their invariable principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPRA, therefore, fought stubbornly without losing confidence in victory even in manifold hardships and achieved national liberation.
 Thanks to the tradition of supporting army and helping people, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea defeated the U.S. imperialists who boasted of being "the strongest" in the world in the past Fatherland Liberation War. And today it firmly safeguards the dignity of the nation in a war without gunfire against imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year, too, the army and people of the DPRK will display to the full the traditional beautiful trait of supporting army and helping people and defend the socialist motherland as an impregnable fortress.

Great Revolutionary Activity, Inspiration to People
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il visited the newly constructed e-library and gymnasium of Kim Chaek University of Technology, appreciated the New Year's Performance "Blue Sky over My County" and met talented children of Ponbu Kindergarten in Sinuiju City from the beginning of the year following his field guidance he gave throughout last year to vigorously arouse the army and people to the construction of a great prosperous powerful nation. The news of his energetic revolutionary activities encourages the servicepersons and people on the general onward march of the Songun revolution to a higher leap.
 Boundlessly inspired by his revolutionary activities, the officers and men of the Korean People's Army are full of a firm resolution to demonstrate to the full the might of the revolutionary powerful army of Mt. Paektu defending the leader with their lives, to follow the Songun idea and defend and implement the Songun politics in the van of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the Ministry of Agriculture and officials and working people in the field of agriculture including the Mangyongdae Farm of Mangyongdae District, Pyongyang, are also filled with the confidence that they can do anything when they advance forward toward the bright morrow under the guidance of Kim Jong Il, the brilliant commander of Songun. They are now putting spurs to farming preparation to yield a bumper harvest on the socialist co-op fields this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers in the Pukchang Thermal-power Complex, the Tokchon Area Coal Complex, the Musan Mining Complex, the Pyongyang Steel Plant and in other units of key industries are effecting a production upswing in their working sites in accordance with the leader's intention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are gaining courage from the news of the great revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Il, who wisely leads the efforts to defend socialism and build a great prosperous powerful nation for the prosperity of the country and the happiness of the people, and are sure to make a higher leap this year, too, full of a great ambition and confidence.

Wreaths Placed before Bust of Kim Hyong Gwon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 12 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of Kim Hyong Gwon, ardent revolutionary fighter, in the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on the occasion of his 70th death anniversary Thursday.
 Seen standing there was a wreath sent by Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, officials of the ministries, national institutions, working people's organizations and media organizations and working people in the city. 
 Also laid there were wreaths in the name of ministries, national institutions, working people's organizations and media organizations.
 The ribbons of the wreaths bore letters "In memory of Revolutionary Fighter Comrade Kim Hyong Gwon". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to Kim Hyong Gwon, ardent patriot and staunch revolutionary, who dedicated his precious life to the liberation of Korea and the victory of the revolution true to the leadership of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths, bouquets and flowers were also placed before his statues in Kim Hyong Gwon County and Hongwon County on the same day.
